<h2>Mission Statement</h2>
<p>The Recreation Management area provides students life enhancing  skills and wisdom to make wholesome recreation choices regarding  personal and family leisure time. Students receive outstanding  leadership training through adventure education. Majors receive  professional preparation for career opportunities. The unique natural  resources of the region and department's experiential teaching  philosophy provide students with opportunities for personal growth,  enhanced self-esteem, ability to manage risk and the development of  strong resource protection and service ethics.</p>
